---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const lang = 'en-us';
const post = {
  title: 'Wild Oases',
  subtitle: 'Beaches Reachable Only by Sea',
  category: 'GUIDE',
  date: 'April 28, 2026',
  readTime: '9 min',
  image: '/images/spiagge-selvagge.jpg',
  imageAlt: 'Wild Oases: wild beaches reachable only by sea on the Amalfi Coast',
  path: '/en-us/blog/wild-remote-beaches/',
};

const metaTitle = "Wild Oases: Amalfi Coast Beaches Reachable Only by Sea | Guide 2026";
const metaDescription = "Discover the most remote beaches on the Amalfi Coast, accessible only by sea. Santa Croce at Amalfi, Cavallo Morto at Maiori, La Vite: the authentic oases.";

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/en-us/' },
  { name: 'Blog', url: '/en-us/blog/' },
  { name: 'Wild Oases', url: '/en-us/blog/wild-remote-beaches/' },
];

const quickInfo = [
  { label: 'Beaches reached', value: 'Only by sea · Private boat or tour' },
  { label: 'Type of access', value: 'Hidden coves between cliffs' },
  { label: 'Services', value: 'Absent or mini-bar/restaurant' },
  { label: 'Specialty', value: 'Crystal clear water, underwater springs' },
  { label: 'Ideal for', value: 'Those seeking isolation and authenticity' },
  { label: 'Best period', value: 'May-September, calm sea' },
  { label: 'Recommended equipment', value: 'Snorkel, underwater camera' },
  { label: 'Atmosphere', value: 'Wild, silent, primordial' },
];

const faq = [
  {
    q: 'How are these beaches reached?',
    a: 'Exclusively by sea. The most authentic solution is to rent a traditional Sorrento gozzo with a local skipper from Amalfi or the small ports of the Coast. Alternatively, organized excursions exist from the main coastal cities.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Are they really difficult to reach?',
    a: 'No, if you have a boat or join an excursion. Difficult to reach on foot: the rock walls are insurmountable. But once in a boat, navigation is simple and the sea is generally calm from May to September.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Are there services on the beach?',
    a: 'It depends. Santa Croce has two restaurants with beach club service. Cavallo Morto is completely wild, without services. La Vite has a small beach club-restaurant. We recommend bringing plenty of water and food for the free beaches.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the best time to visit them?',
    a: 'May-September, when the sea is calm and navigation safe. Avoid winter months due to risk of strong waves. June and September are ideal: less crowded than August, but with excellent weather.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I swim and snorkel?',
    a: 'Absolutely yes. The water is crystalline and underwater visibility is excellent. Bring a snorkel mask: you will see rocky seabeds and intact marine flora. Perfect for novice divers.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is it dangerous to go with children?',
    a: 'If the sea is calm (check forecasts), it is relatively safe with children on board. Once on the beach, the coves are sheltered and the water is tranquil. Discouraged only in case of waves.',
  },
];

const sidebarLinks = [
  { label: 'Comfortable and equipped beaches', href: '/en-us/blog/comfortable-beaches/' },
  { label: 'Where to watch the sunset', href: '/en-us/blog/sunset-beaches/' },
  { label: 'All Amalfi Coast beaches', href: '/en-us/beaches/' },
  { label: 'When to visit', href: '/en-us/when-to-visit/' },
  { label: 'Getting here', href: '/en-us/getting-here/' },
];

const authorRole = 'Beach & Adventure Guide · Amalfi Coast';

const relatedArticles = [
  {
    title: 'Comfort and Relaxation',
    category: 'GUIDE',
    date: 'April 28, 2026',
    image: '/images/spiagge-bambini.jpg',
    imageAlt: 'Comfort and Relaxation: Accessible and equipped beaches on the Amalfi Coast',
    path: '/en-us/blog/comfortable-beaches/'
  },
  {
    title: 'Golden Hour Sunsets',
    category: 'GUIDE',
    date: 'April 28, 2026',
    image: '/images/tramonto-costiera.jpg',
    imageAlt: 'Golden Hour Sunsets: Sunset on the Amalfi Coast with golden reflections on the sea',
    path: '/en-us/blog/sunset-beaches/'
  }
];

const blogSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BlogPosting",
  "headline": "Wild Oases: Beaches Reachable Only by Sea",
  "image": "/images/spiagge-selvagge.jpg",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-28",
  "dateModified": "2026-04-28",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Amalfi Coast Travel"
  },
  "description": "Discover the most remote and wild beaches on the Amalfi Coast, accessible only by sea. Santa Croce, Cavallo Morto, La Vite: the authentic oases of the Tyrrhenian Sea."
};

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": faq.map(item => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": item.q,
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": item.a
    }
  }))
};
---

<BlogPostLayout
  lang={lang}
  post={post}
  metaTitle={metaTitle}
  metaDescription={metaDescription}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  quickInfo={quickInfo}
  faq={faq}
  sidebarLinks={sidebarLinks}
  authorRole={authorRole}
  relatedArticles={relatedArticles}
>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <div>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6 font-light">
      The true luxury, in a territory famous and frequented like the Amalfi Coast, does not lie in the most exclusive beach clubs or the terraces of five-star resorts, but in the almost surreal silence of a hidden cove that knows neither the noise of cars nor the frantic passage of mass tourism. Along the jagged coastline that winds between Amalfi and the promontory of Capo d'Orso, nature has sculpted small masterpieces of rock and pebbles protected by vertical walls insurmountable, accessible exclusively by sailing the crystal clear waters of the Tyrrhenian Sea.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Santa Croce -->
  <div>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Santa Croce: The Most Celebrated Pearl</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Santa Croce beach, located just minutes by boat from the Amalfi pier, is undoubtedly the most celebrated among these hidden gems. It takes its name from the remains of an ancient medieval chapel dedicated to Santa Croce, of which traces can still be seen among the Mediterranean scrub. It is a paradise of light pebbles that reflect sunlight making the water crystal clear, ideal for those who love swimming offshore or snorkeling along the cliff edges.
    </p>
    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Why It's Special</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        Although most of the shoreline is occupied by two historic restaurants offering beach club service and excellent local cuisine, there is a small stretch of free beach for those preferring a more rustic and autonomous contact with nature.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Cavallo Morto -->
  <div>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Cavallo Morto: Remote and Spectacular</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Even more remote and wild is Cavallo Morto beach, also known as Bellavaia, located in Maiori territory. Despite its sinister name, linked to old local legends, it is one of the most spectacular beaches in the entire region. Being southeast-facing, it is the first to receive sun rays at dawn, offering a unique chromatic spectacle as the sea grades to a deep cobalt blue.
    </p>
    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Pure Experience</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        This beach is completely free and devoid of any services: there are no bars, no umbrella rentals. It is the ultimate destination for those seeking total isolation and wanting to immerse themselves in a primordial context.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- La Vite -->
  <div>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">La Vite: Unspoiled Nature</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Finally, La Vite merits mention, a bay sheltered in the municipality of Conca dei Marini. A strip of pebbles set among towering rocks where nature reigns supreme. Here you will find a harmonious mix: part is managed by a small beach club-restaurant that seems suspended above the waves, but there is an area of free beach where you can spread your towel and enjoy the sea in total tranquility.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Consigli -->
  <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-[2rem] shadow-xl border border-slate-100">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-med-gold flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M9 18h6"/><path d="M10 22h4"/><path d="M15.09 14c.18-.98.65-1.74 1.41-2.5A4.65 4.65 0 0 0 18 8 6 6 0 0 0 6 8c0 1 .23 2.23 1.5 3.5A4.61 4.61 0 0 1 8.91 14"/></svg>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Practical Tips</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Fundamental Logistics</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Bring plenty of water and food with you, since many of these coves have no refreshment points and sun reflection on white rocks drastically raises the perceived temperature.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">The Authentic Experience</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The most authentic way to experience them is to rent a traditional Sorrento gozzo with a local skipper. Don't just ask to be left on the shore: ask them to show you adjacent sea caves, like the Arch of Lovers.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Recommended Equipment</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Snorkel and diving mask are essential. The water is so crystalline you will see rocky seabeds at surprising depths. Also bring an underwater camera to capture the marine flora.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</BlogPostLayout>
